result.name: Sushi Masataka

reviews.text: Though I haven't been to a lot of extravagant sushi restaurants, I am still pretty confident that this is one of the best to come by in this locality. Attention down to the details with innovative preparation of food. Every bite you can taste as if the chef's 30 years of experience concentrated into a drop. Super friendly chef and staff, and it was absolutely magical watching Chef Masa-san's clockwork cooking skills. Absolutely amazing experience.

The best omakase I ever tried in HK. Every course is like an art piece made with fresh and seasonal ingredients. I enjoy watching the cooking performance of Chef Masa throughout the 2-hour dining. Chef and staffs are all amazing and professional. Worth to visit again.
Think it’s the best sushi table in Hong Kong, low key location.  Fresh and excellent across the board including regional specialties like hairy crab - if not creative.  Valet parking available
Good food quality, but relatively over priced.

Exquisite sushi experience with top notch service and intimate ambiance- one feels teleported to Japan. The Omakase menu on the pricier side and focuses mainly on fresh sushi instead of courses followed by other phases. It’s worth it for a special event.
